═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  admin_keys/ — Admin Console Public Key (Compile-Time)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  This directory holds the Ed25519 PUBLIC key for admin console
  authentication. It is embedded into the unikernel binary at
  build time via include_str!() in src/admin/auth.rs.

  Files:
    admin_pub.pem   ← Ed25519 public key (safe to commit)

  The corresponding PRIVATE key (admin_priv.pem) lives in the
  project root and is gitignored. Keep it on your workstation.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  HOW AUTHENTICATION WORKS
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  1. Open https://<appliance>/admin/ in your browser
  2. Select your admin_priv.pem file when prompted
  3. The browser signs a server challenge using Web Crypto API
  4. The server verifies the signature against this public key
  5. If valid, you get a session token (1-hour expiry)

  No passwords. No credentials stored on the server.
  The private key never leaves your machine.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  GENERATING NEW KEYS
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Run the included script:

    ./scripts/gen-admin-keys.sh

  This generates:
    admin_keys/admin_pub.pem  ← Rebuild to embed the new key
    admin_priv.pem            ← Keep this safe, never commit

  After generating new keys, rebuild the binary to embed the
  new public key. The old private key will no longer work.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
